# PHP WHMCS Module — nextcloudsaas

## File layout
- `nextcloudsaas.php`: WHMCS callbacks only (`nextcloudsaas_MetaData`, `CreateAccount`, admin buttons)
- `lib/Helper.php`: pure utilities, DNS, parsing, constants (`CONTAINER_SUFFIXES`, `SHARED_CONTAINERS`)
- `lib/SSHManager.php`: SSH + `manage.sh` + docker/occ — single remote integration point
- `lib/NextcloudAPI.php`: OCS HTTP client (cURL); fallback to SSH occ when SSL not ready
- `includes/hooks/nextcloudsaas_hooks.php`: cron DNS, checkout, AcceptOrder, emails

## Patterns
- Namespace `NextcloudSaaS` for lib classes; WHMCS callbacks stay global functions
- SSH commands: wrap with `sudo -n`; never interpolate raw user input into shell
- `fromWhmcsParams()` for SSHManager construction — do not duplicate server config parsing
- Custom field lookup: use `nextcloudsaas_findDomainCustomField()` in hooks (v3.1.7 cascade)
- After successful provision: call `nextcloudsaas_acceptOrderForService()` to close Pending orders

## Architecture constants (v11.x contract)
- 3 dedicated containers per client: `app`, `cron`, `harp`
- 8 shared services: `shared-db`, `shared-redis`, `shared-collabora`, `shared-turn`, `shared-nats`, `shared-janus`, `shared-signaling`, `shared-recording`
- 1 DNS A record per client (main domain only)

## Testing
- Tests live in `tests/` with separate `composer.json` — never require full WHMCS bootstrap
- `tests/bootstrap.php` provides Capsule stub; extend stubs before adding DB-dependent tests
- Helper contract tests must stay fast and offline (no SSH, no DNS network unless mocked)

## Anti-patterns
- Do not add Laravel/Symfony dependencies to the module vendor
- Do not expose HaRP shared key in `clientarea.tpl`
- Do not treat `.env` alone as fully provisioned instance (`instanceExists` requires `.credentials` + `app` container)
- Do not hardcode Collabora/TURN hostnames per client — use `Helper::getSharedHostnames()`
